name: Rocket Propulsion
description: This course provides an in-depth study of the fundamentals of rocket propulsion, covering topics such as propulsion theory, engine types, fuel chemistry, and the practical applications of rocket technology. Designed for students with a strong background in physics and engineering, the course includes both theoretical instruction and hands-on laboratory work

name: Aerodynamics
description: This course offers a comprehensive exploration of aerodynamics, focusing on the principles and applications of airflow and its effects on flying objects. Topics include fluid dynamics, airfoil design, lift and drag forces, and the aerodynamic considerations in aircraft design. The course blends theoretical learning with practical applications, suitable for students pursuing a career in aeronautics or astronautics engineering.

name: Spacecraft Design
description: This course delves into the principles and practices of spacecraft design, offering students a detailed understanding of the engineering and technology behind spacecraft systems. Key topics include spacecraft structure, propulsion, power systems, thermal control, and payload integration. Emphasizing both theoretical concepts and practical skills, the course prepares students for careers in the space industry, with a focus on innovative design and problem-solving in the context of current and future space missions

name: Atlantis
description: Atlantis is an under water city in the DC Universe. Students will learn about the mechanisms of underwater breathing and swimming. An Atlantian is placed on problem-solving dashboard in the laboratory, preparing students for advanced studies in atlantian organics, and related fields.

name: Wakanda
description: This course deals with the history of the prominent nation of Wakanda.

name: Stark Tower
description: This course introduces students to the architecture and idea behind the stark tower which houses billionaire Tony Stark and Pepper Potts.The course also provides a comprehensive understanding of behavior, reaction dynamics, and the application of mathematical methods in solving construction problems.

name: Web Development
description: This course offers an exploration of the web technologies and languages including frameworks involved in the course.
author: 654f9ec2ea7ead465908d1e3

name: Agriculture
description: This course explores the complex relationships and diplomatic interactions among the different agricultural practices of earth. Students will engage in discussions and case studies on key events in earth's agriculture history.
author: 654f9ec2ea7ead465908d1e3

name: Alphabet
description: This course delves into the history in the making of alphabet, examining the sources, practitioners, and manifestations of its technologies. The course combines theoretical study with practical insights, offering a unique perspective on the decisions involved that led to this event.
author: 654f9ec2ea7ead465908d1e3

name: Boston Tea Party
description: This course examines the foundations of boston tea party and the traditions connected to this event. Students will engage in discussions on the challenges and opportunities of participating in this event in current setting

name: Meteor JS
description: This course provides an in-depth analysis of the Meteor JS framework with a focus on web development. The course encourages students to critically examine the concepts of web dev.

name: Quantum Computing
description: Focusing on the early quantum computing technologies, this course explores innovative educational practices and theories of the time. Students will study the evolution of educational methods, the integration of practical and theoretical knowledge, and the role of quantum computing.

name: Virtual Reality
description: This course explores the core principles of Virtual Reality. Students will examine devlopment techniques through the lens of Technical means, learning to apply these principles in various real-life contexts. The course encourages critical thinking.
author: 65500111ea7ead465908d1fa

name: Sky High
description: This historical course delves into the development of early institution called Sky High. It focuses on the life and teachings of Meta humans, the role of the super heroes, and the spread of powers across the world Students will understand the challenges and triumphs of the early powers.
author: 65500111ea7ead465908d1fa

name: Database Management
description: This course offers insights into Database Management Systems. Topics include sql, mongodb and the er diagrams. Students will engage in practical exercises and discussions, preparing them for various roles in database administration.
author: 65500111ea7ead465908d1fa

name: Hogwarts
description: This course delves into the rich and profound world of Sorcery, exploring its philosophical underpinnings, mystical practices, and historical development. The course also examines various spells, their rituals, and contributions to Magic.
author: 655000a4ea7ead465908d1f5

name: Four Horsemen
description: Focusing on the ethical dimensions of Magic, this course examines the teachings and wisdom found in the Four horsemen, with a special emphasis on Daniel atlas.
author: 655000a4ea7ead465908d1f5

name: Silicon Valley
description: This advanced course explores the world of tech in silicon valley, delving into topics such as the data compression and the role of high internet speeds.
author: 655000a4ea7ead465908d1f5

name: Augumented Reality
description: This course explores the principles and practices of Augumented Reality in Tech industry. The course also delves into the integration of these practices with modern tech.

name: Axe Capital
description: This course introduces students to the history and heirarchy of Axe Capital Investments, the company of investment bankers.

name: Asgard
description: This course introduces students to the history and heirarchy of Asgard, the city of asgardians
